&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursing Vacancies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division of Surgery and Planned Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nursing Vacancies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division of Surgery and Planned Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rotherham Foundation Trust has within the division of surgery and planned care. A number of exciting opportunities available for Band 5 Staff Nurses It is a really exciting time here at The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We currently have vacancies across our surgical wards and departments, including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B5 non-elective surgical ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Acute Surgical Unit (ASU)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keppel Elective surgical ward&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**STOP PRESS**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to reconfiguration the elective ward is moving to a new larger ward. From Monday August 10th we will be relocated to Keppel ward. This means I can now recruit a further 8 staff nurses to this normally fully staffed unit. The elective ward offers tremendous learning opportunities and is managed by our proactive manager Sister Sally Short.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The other 2 wards, ASU and B5 only have minimal vacancies which shows the excellent teams and working environment. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why not call for an informal chat to discuss further. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A career within a surgical environment offers a wide range of learning opportunities and our Ward Managers will work with you to create your own individualized development plan. This does include a certain element of flexible working where appropriate. The surgical unit has undergone substantial development and staff wellbeing and training are at the forefront of the Matron’s itinerary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All staff are actively encouraged to progress with all extended skills in order to become autonomous practitioners within a great team environment. Whilst senior support is available at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A new surgical training program commences in Sept 2020 with a monthly study day that all staff will attend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are in the enviable position of only having minimal vacancies in these areas now. This is due to the excellent teamwork within the surgical division. Vast training opportunities and excellent career progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rotherham Foundation Trust is renowned for being #thereallyfriendlytrust. We fully support informal visits/enquiries, if applying via NHS Jobs please specify on the personal statement section the ward you are interested in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat and tour of the departments please contact -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron Lee White &lt;/strong&gt;lee.white6@nhs.net&lt;strong&gt; 01709425815. Please do contact me and I will make time to meet you in person to discuss requirements.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
